    "MissionGiver": "Citizens for Prosperity",
    "Title": "Reclaim Stolen Cargo",
    "Description": "Hey,\n\nOutlaws used a fake distress beacon to lure one of our cargo ships into a trap and steal the supplies onboard. Thankfully, we placed trackers in the cargo containers, because the stuff is valuable mining and construction materials needed at ~mission(Destination). \n\nLooks like the goods ended up at ~mission(Location|Address). Need someone to head there, reclaim the supplies, and take them to ~mission(Destination|Address). Doubt they\u2019ll make it easy for you, but if it helps, they didn\u2019t show any mercy to our ship crew. Reclaiming those supplies will not only help the CFP but ensure that our crew didn\u2019t die in vain.   \n\nAlso, to make your life easier, I'd make sure you have a <EM4>handheld tractor beam</EM4> with you. \n\nThanks,\n\nLima Endicott\nLead Dispatcher\nCitizens for Prosperity",
    "DisplayDescription": "Hey,\n\nOutlaws used a fake distress beacon to lure one of our cargo ships into a trap and steal the supplies onboard. Thankfully, we placed trackers in the cargo containers, because the stuff is valuable mining and construction materials needed at Canard View. \n\nLooks like the goods ended up at [Location|Address]. Need someone to head there, reclaim the supplies, and take them to Canard View. Doubt they\u2019ll make it easy for you, but if it helps, they didn\u2019t show any mercy to our ship crew. Reclaiming those supplies will not only help the CFP but ensure that our crew didn\u2019t die in vain.   \n\nAlso, to make your life easier, I'd make sure you have a <EM4>handheld tractor beam</EM4> with you. \n\nThanks,\n\nLima Endicott\nLead Dispatcher\nCitizens for Prosperity",
